ShortName: Paper & proof conventions
Topic: arithmetic-and-algebra
Concepts: The unexplained reading conventions of a methods section: iid (same jar, separate draws) and why papers state it, theorem/lemma/corollary/proof + the QED box (trust the boxed result, skip the proof), the ritual phrases ("it follows that", "WLOG", "it suffices to show", "by construction"), asymptotics in words ("as $n\to\infty$", consistency, big-O as a growth/shrink rate — reading level), assumption lists (where methods state conditions and why you check them), and the model → estimation → inference → validation anatomy as a reading map
BuildsOn: [reading-math-notation](reading-math-notation/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: —
